extends /components/creative-base.pug

block variable
  - var page_title = 'Fractal Trees'

block page_script
  script(type='module').
    import execute from '@/scripts/creative_coding/generation/fractal/fractal_tree_curve/index.js';
    const root = document.getElementById('fractral-tree-curve');
    execute().start(root.querySelector('#canvas'), root.querySelector('#config'));

block canvas_container
  +canvasContainer({ id: 'fractral-tree-curve', canvasId: 'canvas', width: 500, height: 500, hasConfig: true })
    +buttonInput({ id: 'set', label: 'Regenerate' })
    +buttonInput({ id: 'box', label: 'Toggle Box' })
    +buttonInput({ id: 'reset', label: 'Restart' })

block page_description
  p.
    The #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_sequence') Fibonacci spiral]: an approximation of the golden spiral created by drawing circular arcs connecting the opposite corners of squares in the Fibonacci tiling.
  p.
    <strong>How to interact:</strong>
  ul
    li <strong>Regenerate:</strong> Create a new random variation
    li <strong>Toggle Box:</strong> Show/hide the underlying square grid
    li <strong>Restart:</strong> Reset the animation to the beginning
  p.
    The algorithm divides space using Fibonacci numbers (1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13...),
    with each iteration creating smaller rectangles following the golden ratio φ ≈ 1.618.
    This spiral appears in nautilus shells, sunflower seed patterns, galaxy arms, and many other natural formations.
